social_posts.post_text:
Welcoming our newest OAC team member @josettenorris!

Josette is a huge talent that comes with PB’s of 3:59 for 1500m and 14:51 for 5000m. 

We’ve been working hard already and she’s an amazing addition to the women’s team. We’ve got an awesome group around her to push to next level. I can’t wait to help her chase her dreams! 

#onathleticsclub #OAC @on_running

Beautiful long run this morning on the dirt roads. The team is looking strong coming into the indoor season!

#onathleticsclub #OAC @on_running 📸 @colinnwong

🗣️ “Man…it was amazing. @millrosegames is our place I guess! I love this meet. The energy is like unlike anything else at the @armorynyc. Last year, we came with four people and won three races and had some PBs…This year, it was hard to think we were going to top it. We came in with 10 and the team is just crushing.” 

A solid day at work for coach @djritzenhein and the On Athletic Club.

It’s hard for me to put into words just how amazing this weekend was for the team. How could we top @millrosegames from last year?! 

But they did, 7 Nationals records!! Two victories. These 10 athletes all represented at such a high level. 

The team behind the team is what makes this possible. Thank you for those in support of us and in our corner. You know what it takes to make performances like these. Having that support is something I’ll never take for granted. A true team effort from everyone. This is an all-star team from all over the world training to push each other to new limits. I’m very proud to be their coach! There’s no limit to what they can do. #OAC #onathleticsclub @on_running

📸1-4 @kevmofoto 
📸5-6 @pacephoto 
📸7-10 @justinbritton

This past week has been a blur! It’s exciting and energizing to see the team focused and working hard. We’ve been back to the basics with some big weeks. But we’re still having fun and learning new skills. #onathleticsclub #OAC @on_running

I’m working on three years with these boys. They have gotten stronger and faster each year. We have big goals these coming seasons but I always try to remember to have somewhere to go for them year after year. We focus on building with consistency and becoming resilient over everything else. The stronger the foundation the longer you’ll last.

#OAC #onathleticsclub @on_running

What an incredible moment yesterday! @hellenobiri the @bostonmarathon champion! 

I couldn’t be more happy and proud of her! She was so determined and focused. It took a bit convincing to run this race after the last marathon but I knew she was ready for it. But I wanted her to be one to decide to do it. She made that decision and went all in. We made the plan and she executed to perfection. She wanted this one so badly. Watching her flying down Boylston street and to see her with her family at the end so emotional is what this is all about! 

📸 @justinbritton 

#OAC #onathleticsclub @on_running

Busy day at the track! Sunday mornings at the track are my favorite time of the week. The team is looking good heading into @pennrelays and @soundrunning Trackfest these next few weeks. High training volumes still with the early season, but looking forward to a few races to get this season started.

#OAC #onathleticsclub @on_running

location.city_name: St. Moritz Top of the world

social_posts.post_text: Chasing the team around Europe. I’ve been putting in good miles too just to keep up with them! Great training, awesome races so far and they have really been putting in amazing work. The team is focused and ready for a big summer! Next up Paris and Oslo.

After an extensive search I am very excited that we have found our new assistant coach for the OAC,  @coachkquinn! 

Kelsey Quinn comes to us with an incredible skill set and years of experience. 

So much hard work has gone into building the team to this point, so putting the right support system behind our athletes for the long haul has been the number one goal this year. Kelsey will be a huge help to me with our growing roster. I look forward to having her assistance and expertise as we work to elevate the OAC as they chase their dreams! 

#Dreamon #OAC #onathleticsclub @on_running

Pretty epic weekend! Highlights @yaredthegoose winning our first OAC @diamondleagueathletics meeting in London! Many second places these last two year but this was the first. 

@monsonalicia with an incredible American Record of 14:19.45 in the 5000m. I knew this one was in there but just so awesome to see if front row. She was so tough as always!

And @georgebeamish broke the 38 year old New Zealand Steeplechase record running 8:13.26 in @diamondleaguemonaco. Amazing how fast he’s developing in his first season with this event.

Now up to St. Moritz for the last three weeks of prep before Budapest.

📸 @michaeldawson.nz 

#OAC #onathleticsclub @on_running

Heading out from Budapest very happy and proud of the teams efforts and results at the World Championships these last 10 days. 

We had four top 6 finishes in the finals led by Alicia 5th in 10k, George 5th in the steeplechase, Yared in 5th and Mario 6th in the 1500m. A PR of 4:01 in the 1500m from Sinta, a first world champs 5k for Jonas, Morgan back in the 5k after injury last year and Joe third consecutive global 10k team. 8 total OAC athletes and half in the top 6 in the world in their events. It was huge step forward for the team in its third year and I couldn’t be happier with the way they competed at this champs. 

Experience matters so much and these global championships are something unlike any other event all year for athletes. It can be very long and exhausting for everyone involved.

A big shoutout to their federation staff as they really were amazing help for them and me. And I am very thankful for our team at @on and @drjasonross for supporting all our athletes throughout this week and a half. It was a lot of long nights but so worth it. 

A few weeks left in the season and we’re ready to finish it strong!
📸 @jzsnapz 
#OAC #onathleticsclub

I have the best job in the world! It’s a nonstop express train all summer with the most amazing group of athletes. Sometimes it’s a blur but looking back helps me appreciate what I get to do everyday. Now, time to go home to see my loved ones, finish the season strong and get everyone ready for the next adventure! #blessed 
#OAC #onathleticsclub @on

NYC Marathon Champion!! What an incredible day!

After last years debut coming back here had so much meaning. What a difference a year makes. Her family was waiting for her at the end this time and it was such special feeling to see her redemption.

Hellen is one of a kind, the ultimate competitor. So proud of her!

📸 @justinbritton
